\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 Covariates\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 Data on age, sex, body mass index (BMI), physical activity level, alcohol consumption, perceived stress, and dietary habits were collected using standardized questionnaires. These variables were included as covariates in the statistical analyses.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 Statistical Analysis\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 Continuous variables were expressed as mean \'b1 standard deviation. Differences between sleep duration groups were assessed using one-way analysis of variance (ANOVA) followed by post hoc tests. Multivariate linear regression models were used to assess associations between sleep duration and immune markers after adjusting for covariates. A p-value < 0.05 was considered statistically significant.\
