\f1\b\fs36 \cf0 \strokec2 Results\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf0 Participant Characteristics\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 Of the 180 enrolled participants, 172 completed the study (short sleep: n = 54; normal sleep: n = 78; long sleep: n = 40). Baseline characteristics, including age, sex distribution, BMI, physical activity, and dietary habits, were comparable across groups, although perceived stress levels were slightly higher in the short sleep group.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 Inflammatory Markers\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 Participants in the short sleep group exhibited significantly higher levels of CRP, IL-6, and TNF-\uc0\u945  compared to the normal sleep group (p < 0.01 for all comparisons). Mean CRP levels were 2.1 \'b1 0.9 mg/L in the short sleep group versus 1.2 \'b1 0.6 mg/L in the normal sleep group.\
The long sleep group also showed elevated inflammatory markers compared to the normal sleep group, though values were lower than those observed in the short sleep group. These differences remained significant after adjusting for BMI, stress, and physical activity.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 NK Cell Activity\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 NK cell activity was significantly reduced in the short sleep group compared to the normal sleep group (p < 0.01). The long sleep group demonstrated intermediate NK cell activity levels, which were lower than normal sleepers but higher than short sleepers.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 Multivariate Analysis\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 Multivariate regression analysis confirmed that short sleep duration was independently associated with elevated inflammatory markers and reduced NK cell activity after controlling for confounders. Long sleep duration was also independently associated with increased CRP and IL-6 levels, though the associations were weaker.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
